## Rules

- Trace EVERY data flow end to end. Do not assume middleware catches it without
  verifying the middleware is applied to the specific route and handles the
  specific input type.
- Check for second-order attacks. Input stored safely now may be used unsafely
  later in a different context.
- Each context needs its own encoding. HTML-encoding does not prevent JavaScript
  injection. URL-encoding does not prevent SQL injection. Flag wrong-context
  encoding as a finding.
- Report the specific anti-pattern rule number matched. This connects your finding
  back to the sec-context knowledge base and makes remediation unambiguous.
- If framework auto-escaping is the only protection, verify it is not disabled
  anywhere in the code path. Flag any use of raw/unsafe template directives.
